We celebrated an enchanting evening of artistry and heritage with RangRaas, a captivating collaboration between National Award-winning textile artist Gaurang Shah and the iconic Kishandas & Co., renowned since 1875 for their exquisite jewellery.
Gaurang’s mastery of the Jamdani weave, innovative use of moga yarn, pure zari, and silk brought traditional techniques into the modern era, while Kishandas & Co. showcased heirloom jewellery that seamlessly blended royal elegance with contemporary flair. It was a sensory celebration of color, texture, and tradition, paired with the luxurious legacy of Hyderabad’s finest jewels. Guests were immersed in the magic of RangRaas that unforgettable evening!

#BTFW24 #BTFW #TFW

Revivalist designer Pankaj S., in collaboration with Meghashrey NGO, led by the dedicated philanthropist Seema Singh, proudly presents The Timeless Heirlooms of India at #BombayTimesFashionWeek24. For nearly a decade, Pankaj S. has travelled across India, reviving and preserving the country’s fading embroidery and weaving traditions. This exquisite collection showcases age-old craftsmanship, featuring real gold and silver wire embroidery once revered by royalty.
It’s a tribute to India’s rich heritage. A museum-worthy celebration of pure luxury. Together, Pankaj S. and Meghashrey unite to raise awareness for education, healthcare, and sustainable development.

#BTFW24 #BTFW #TFW
#BombayTimesFashionWeek24 #fashionweek #fashionshow #SurprisingYou

In a mesmerising ode to birds-especially the hummingbird-Aves by Anusha Reddy emerged as a timeless collection that embodied effortless movement, lightness, and refined elegance. Each piece in this ethereal collection showcased feather-like embellishments, structured bodices, and fluid skirts that flowed with grace.
Aves harmoniously blended modern design with the enduring beauty of nature, crafting garments that celebrated the breathtaking allure of flight and the fluidity of movement. The collection transcended fashion, inviting all to embrace the true artistry of nature.

Step into the world of The Royaleum by Hetal Shah, where love, tradition, and timeless elegance come together. Discover the Royaleum’s Rangrez 2024 collection, debuting at Bombay Times Fashion Week.

Ruhaaniyat by Sheetal Batra - a collection that captured the soul of Kashmir’s cultural legacy. Each piece is a tribute to traditional craftsmanship, blending Kashmiri tilla art with fine dabka zardozi and Basra pearls. Reimagined on pure silk and adorned with jewel tones, Ruhaaniyat merges heritage with haute couture, creating timeless, elegant silhouettes that speak to the essence of artisanal luxury.

#BTFW24 #BTFW #TFW

The magic of Sonali Jain’s Dhoom Dhadaka Wedding was experienced in a bridal collection that brought the vibrant essence of Indian weddings to life with opulent, festive designs. From Haldi’s sunny hues to the regal Pheras and the grand Reception, this collection celebrated love, tradition, and the festive spirit with intricate embroidery and luxurious fabrics.

#BTFW24 #BTFW #TFW
#BombayTimesFashionWeek24 #fashionweek #fashionshow #SurprisingYou

Roohaniyat by Bespokewala was a collection that spoke to the soul, beautifully illustrating the spiritual bond between two lovers. This unique ensemble was perfect for couples who viewed their union as an everlasting celebration of love.

Each piece radiated timeless grace, adorned with intricate mandalas, celestial patterns, and floral motifs handwoven with care. Flowing fabrics interwoven with metallic threads and sequins, along with delicate beadwork, evoked a sense of mysticism. This enchanting collection was more than just fashion; it was a celebration of the profound bond that united two souls in harmony.

#BTFW24 #BTFW #TFW
#BombayTimesFashionWeek24 #fashionweek #fashionshow #SurprisingYou

Prémya by Manishii’s latest collection was unveiled, designed for the modern, conscious woman. These classic silhouettes blended traditional craftsmanship with contemporary elegance, making it a timeless addition to their signature Ivory and Black hand-embroidered pieces. Featuring all-season fabrics and exclusive hand-embroidered motifs, each piece was versatile and could be restyled and reworn year after year. With the addition of deep purple and emerald tones, the collection offered even more evergreen options that paired effortlessly with any jewellery. It was a celebration of Indian handlooms, designed to be both globally inspired and locally made.

#BTFW24 #BTFW #TFW
#BombayTimesFashionWeek24 #fashionweek #fashionshow #SurprisingYou

The magic of BANDHAN by @vastra.malamunde was unveiled at Bombay Times Fashion Week 2024, showcasing the heartfelt collection by Mrs. Mala Munde and Fashion Director Mohit Kapoor. This collection was a beautiful tribute to Mala’s late brother, Jeevan, embodying the deep emotional bond they shared. Each piece told a story of love and remembrance, especially during Rakhi, as Mala skillfully wove her memories into every stitch.
Adorned with exquisite pearls, the sarees in this collection symbolized timeless love and eternal connections. The essence of BANDHAN was truly celebrated on the runway.

#BTFW24 #BTFW #TFW
#BombayTimesFashionWeek24 #fashionweek #fashionshow #SurprisingYou

The “Enchanted” collection by Asra, presented by Sonani Jewels at Bombay Times Fashion Week 2024, transported everyone into a world of whimsy and elegance. Ethereal gowns met with rich ethnic designs, conjuring a fairy tale atmosphere. Every piece featured intricate embroidery, with butterfly motifs and oversized florals, embracing femininity through flowing, graceful silhouettes. Proudly sponsored by Sonani Jewels, who also unveiled their stunning Bridal Collection for modern brides. It was a captivating celebration of timeless elegance and artistry!

#BTFW24 #BTFW #TFW

Presenting the exquisite Aureate Plumage. This mesmerizing collection captured the beauty of nature through fashion, inspired by the vibrant colors and stunning patterns found in bird plumage. Each garment was a unique masterpiece, blending luxurious fabrics with innovative designs.
Meticulously crafted to perfection, Aureate Plumage embodied Hyaat Couture’s commitment to quality and craftsmanship. Whether worn to a grand event or a cozy gathering, this collection offered timeless elegance for every occasion. Explore the magic of Aureate Plumage and let it inspire your fashion journey!

It was a world of mystique and enchantment with The Azrina jewellery collection by Sunita Gupta. Each exquisite piece appeared to have been plucked from the night sky, intricately crafted with rich rubies, stunning emeralds, dazzling diamonds, and polkis.
The collection highlighted delicate metalwork, creating a timeless allure that left all in awe.
